extended_text.content:
Painter-printmaker Jacob Kainen served as the Smithsonian's curator of prints from 1942 to 1970.

At Landfall Press Kainen resurrected an interest in printmaking dating to his days working for the Works Progress Administration during the Depression, but which had been deferred during his tenure at the Smithsonian.

extended_text.content:
A still-life specialist, Erlebacher  combines Renaissance-like precision with an edginess derived from her sexually suggestive arrangements of objects.

"The Egg symbolizes the wholeness and immanence of the universe.  It is also formless, contained and unresolved.  It is the moment before creation.  It is the precursor of sexual growth and activity."
-Martha Mayer Erlebacher
